The paper deals with wireless communication channels and proposes a new method for orthogonal precoding in OFDM systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of time- and frequency-diversity, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The numerical simulations and analysis of performance could also suggest the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
